  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Lead and coordinate with the Tender Team and Main Contractor during tender and post-tender stages.</p></li><li><p>Analyze tender documents, drawings, specifications, and contractual requirements.</p></li><li><p>Oversee quantity take-off, cost planning, and preparation of detailed estimates.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with suppliers and sub-contractors to obtain competitive pricing and finalize costing for tender submission.</p></li><li><p>Prepare, review, and submit tenders including all supporting technical and commercial documents.</p></li><li><p>Arrange and conduct technical meetings, presentations, and clarification sessions with clients, consultants, and Main Contractors.</p></li><li><p>Support Project Director in commercial discussions, negotiations, and closing of deals.</p></li><li><p>Monitor project progress, control budget, and ensure cost alignment with project objectives.</p></li><li><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3></li></ul><ul><li><p>Degree / Diploma in Building, Quantity Surveying, Mechanical / Civil Engineering, or equivalent.</p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>2–3 years</strong> of relevant experience in the construction industry, preferably in building projects in Singapore.</p></li><li><p>Strong interpersonal, communication, and stakeholder management skills.</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently with strong follow-up, decision-making, and closure abilities.</p></li><li><p>A proactive team player with leadership qualities.</p></li></ul>",
